{"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"text":"Some components can be used for ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"layouts"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"anchor":"Colored-Surface","text":"Colored Surface","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Colored backgrounds use surface colors to maximize the contrast with content.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The colors of several OUDS components (for instance ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":") are automatically adjusted if they are placed on ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSColoredSurface","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"To do so, some tokens associated with these specific colors can be customized and are identified with the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Mono","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" suffix (for instance "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"buttonColorBgDefaultEnabledMono","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" of "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OrangeThemeButtonComponentTokensProvider","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":")."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"How-it-works","text":"How it works","level":4,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"According to the color, the "},{"code":"OUDSColoredSurface","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" component adds in SwiftUI environment two flags:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"oudsUseMonochrome"},{"type":"text","text":": to inform a component that needs to use mono version of tokens"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"oudsOnColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":": to inform a component it is placed on colored surface even if the mono is off"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"How-to-use","text":"How to use","level":4,"type":"heading"},{"code":["    \/\/ The folowing view has a colored background \"modeOnStatusPositiveEmphasized\" with","    \/\/ - a text with the color adapted according to the adjusted colorScheme      ","    \/\/ - a button that uses the mono version of tokens","","    \/\/ As view","    OUDSColoredSurface(color: theme.colorModes.modeOnStatusPositiveEmphasized) {","        VStack {","            Text(\"Status Positive Emphasized\")","            .oudsForegroundColor(theme.colors.colorContentDefault)","","            OUDSButton(text: \"Button\") {}","        }","    }","","    \/\/ As view modifier","","    VStack {","        Text(\"Status Positive Emphasized\")","        .oudsForegroundColor(theme.colors.colorContentDefault)","","        OUDSButton(text: \"Button\") {}","    }","    .oudsColoredSurface(theme.colorModes.modeOnStatusPositiveEmphasized)"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Debuging-contrast-ratios","level":5,"text":"Debuging contrast ratios"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some countries set up new laws so as to force companies to have a better accessibility of their digital services."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This is for example the case for France with the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/accessibilite.numerique.gouv.fr\/","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", also named “RGAA”."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The WCAG specifications, for AA level, defines a contrast ratio of 4.5:1 for textual elements (i.e. texts), and 3:1 for non-textual elements (i.e. link’s chevron)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However it is highly recommended for mobile devices to reach AAA level because of the screen sizes and luminosity issues, i.e. 7:1 for texts and 4.5:1 for non-textual elements."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Some components like ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" can be used on ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSColoredSurface","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" ; thus in that case we can know the surface color for a given component on it, and compute the contrast ratio, and in the end display or not warnings.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To do that, some steps must be followed in your component implementation:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Rise the flag to allow debugging (e.g. i #DEBUG mode)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Get the environement variable defined by the colored surface containing the applied color","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the component implementation, add a line of code comparing the color to test and that surface"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Then keep an eye on your logs ; warnings will be added there if WCAG 2.1 3:1, 4.5:1 or 7:1 ratios are not reached, depending to the methods you call","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Rise the flag","#if DEBUG","OUDSWCAG21Ratios.oudsDebugWCAG21Colors = true","#endif","","\/\/ Supposing we are in your component View \/ ViewModifer struct","","\/\/ Get the applied surface color","@Environment(\\.oudsSurfaceColor) var surfaceColor","","\/\/ In the function defining the color to apply, add the line below","\/\/ where colorTokenToApply is the color to apply from a theme:","","\/\/ Non-textual components, in AA","OUDSWCAG21Ratios.debugContrastRatio(colorToApply, surfaceColor, .nonTextual)","","\/\/ Textual components and AAA to check","OUDSWCAG21Ratios.debugContrastRatio(colorToApply, surfaceColor, .AAA)"]},{"text":"Divider","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Divider"},{"text":"How it works","type":"heading","level":4,"anchor":"How-it-works"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A divider is used to separate content elements in a view. Two kinds of divider are proposed:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSHorizontalDivider"},{"text":" To separate elements stacked vertivally (VStask).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSVerticalDivider"},{"text":" To separate elements stacked Horizontally (HStask).","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A divider can be colored using color enumerated in the "},{"code":"OUDSDividerColor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"text":"How to use","type":"heading","level":4,"anchor":"How-to-use"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Add a vertical divider between items","HStack {","    Text(\"Hello wolrd!\")","    OUDSVerticalDivider(color: .brandPrimary)","    Text(\"Happy to see you\")","}","","\/\/ Add an horizontal divider between items","VStack {","    Text(\"Hello wolrd!\")","    OUDSHorizontalDivider(color: .brandPrimary)","    Text(\"Happy to see you\")","}"]}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"path